args: So, this is the Halidom's Halloween\nparty...
Everyone looks like they're enjoying\nthemselves. However...
(I seem to have some lurking admirers.\nI've felt their eyes for quite some time.)
*pant* *pant* Oh no, did I lose her...?
Why are you following me, Althemia?
Whatever you were plotting, now is your\nchance to confess.
Hmph. Silenced by your own guilt.\nPerhaps you're some sort of spy?
It's nothing like that!\nI just, um... *mumble*
I'll need you to speak clearly.
Oh, come on! Are you really going to make\nme spell it out?!
I was admiring your costume, okay?\nIt's beautiful, and you look amazing.\nHappy now?!
I just really like your outfit. The design\nis delicate, but the silhouette screams\n＂look my way!＂
And don't even get me started on the\nspider elements. You'd think it would\nbe creepy, but it's actually really elegant!
S-so anyway, that's why I wanted to get\na good look at your outfit.
You could have just asked, you know.
But...wouldn't it have been weird?\nSomeone standing right in front\nof you, just staring at your clothes?
I prefer that to being stared at in secret.
I'm flattered you like my clothes, Althemia.\nFeel free to look to your heart's content.
The same goes for you, by the way.\nQuit hiding, and come look with her.
All eyes have weight.\nNow, why were YOU watching me?
Well, I saw you at the party, and I thought\nyour costume was super pretty.

So I guess I was just trying to see
how I could look that awesome too!
Especially since Althemia already
nailed it.
I'm just like you. I WANT to look\nas awesome as Odetta. Don't get\nit twisted!
Oh, er, hold on, I'm not angry. I just...\nUrgh. Sorry.
You two were simply charmed by\nmy attire, then?
Yeah! But, um, that's not the only thing...
I was also wondering if it's even possible\nfor me to pull something like that off.
I'm pretty short, and I'm still a kid, and,\num, I'm not very confident, so...
I just don't know if I'd look good in a\ncostume, is all.
I just mean... I lack confidence too.
Yes. It wasn't easy for me to put this\ncostume on.
I still catch myself thinking about how\nmuch better everyone else looks in\ntheir costumes, like I did with Odetta.
But once I mustered up the courage to\nwear this, people actually told me I look\nGOOD in it.
So I think we're actually not the best\njudges of our own appearance.
You're right. There's no need to fret over\nthe details before you put something on.
And furthermore, it's okay if it doesn't\nlook good at first. Costumes hold the\npower to bring you to entirely new worlds.
Yes. Clothes, shoes, accessories; anything\ndifferent from what you usually wear can\nchange your world.
And once your world has changed, it's only\na matter of time before you change too.
I think I understand. I'm still not quite\nused to my vampire costume, but I HAVE\nbeen feeling a bit more alluring...
Exactly! For me, this spidery outfit makes\nme want to catch people in my web, so to\nspeak. Ha ha!
I... I think I get it!
Speaking of catching people, is that how\nyou snuck up on me earlier?

In any case, just remember that you
don't need to force yourself to match
an outfit's energy. Over time, it will
all come together naturally.
It will? Hm... Maybe I CAN be awesome...
You totally can. Let's do it together!
We just have to believe in the magic of our\ncostumes, and the magic in ourselves, too.
The first step to awesomeness is\nwanting it!
I want to look awesome like you guys!
It sounds like you're ready for a costume.
W-well, I'm not very good at sewing...
Don't worry, Pia, I've got you covered.
I'll put together a truly magical\nensemble—one that fills you\nwith confidence!
...The three of us can step into a new world\ntogether. One that's home to versions of\nourselves we can scarcely imagine!
